creator: JANITRI
descriptionHtml:
DAKSH is a Mobile tablet based intelligent labor monitoring tool which not only allows the staff nurse to register and enter vital signs of a pregnant woman but also reminds to monitor the labor vitals, as per the standard intrapartum protocol. An electronic medical record for labor ward.

It also generates alerts in case of complications, based on an inbuilt algorithm. The doctor at a remote location can also view the live labor progress and guide the staff nurse.


Maternity Ward Application
• Alarms for labor vital monitoring
• Complication alert based on vitals entered by the staff nurses
• Intuitive interface for staff nurses
• Automatic generation of simplified partograph
• Integration with labor monitoring device for FHR & Uterine contraction monitoring
• Instant notifications to referral setting in case of a referred patient
• Useful for staff nurse/midwives training


Doctor/OBGYN Application/Dashboard
• Real-time update on patient progress
• Instant guiding to staff nurses
• Real-time FHR & Uterine contraction data view acquired from labor monitoring device
• Labor vital monitoring alarm frequency setting
• Statistics

title: Janitri: for Hospitals

creator: JANITRI
descriptionHtml:
Formerly known as "DAKSH"

Janitri: for Hospitals is a mobile tablet based intelligent labor monitoring tool which not only allows the staff nurse to register and enter vital signs of a pregnant woman but also reminds to monitor the labor vitals, as per the standard intrapartum protocol. An electronic medical record for labor ward.

It also generates alerts in case of complications, based on an inbuilt algorithm. The doctor at a remote location can also view the live labor progress and guide the staff nurse.


Maternity Ward Application
• Alarms for labor vital monitoring
• Complication alert based on vitals entered by the staff nurses
• Intuitive interface for staff nurses
• Automatic generation of simplified partograph
• Integration with labor monitoring device for FHR & Uterine contraction monitoring
• Instant notifications to referral setting in case of a referred patient
• Useful for staff nurse/midwives training
